Elevator shoes also known as shoes with 'shoe lifts' fastened to the inside of any footwear.
[http://www.elevator-shoes.com]

They are shoes which have thickened sections of the insoles (known as "shoelifts") under the heels to make the wearer appear taller. The users of such shoes are almost exclusively men, as increased height has generally positive social ramifications for males in many cultures.
Note: Both Male and Female users often prefer 'shoe lifts'secret height increase inserts.


Unlike high-heeled shoes for women, the component of elevator shoes that increases the wearer's height is inside the shoe, making it almost invisible to observers. Most men who wear such shoes prefer to keep that fact a secret from others.

Women tend to simply prefer 'shoe lifts' that are easily transferable between footwear.
[http://www.elevator-shoes.com]

Shoes with thickened soles are also used in cases of orthopaedic problems, although the phrase "elevator shoe" is not usually used for these. The terms 'heel lifts' and 'shoe inserts' would appear more common.